article.headline: Oregon State 72, USC 67
article.story:
CORVALLIS, Ore. (AP) -- Shannon Howell scored 24 points and Brina
Chaney added 11 points and 12 rebounds to lead Oregon State to a
come-from-behind victory over Southern California Sunday.

It was the third straight victory for the Beavers (9-4, 3-1),
who haven't opened 3-1 in the Pacific-10 Conference since 1999-00.

Ebony Hoffman had 14 points and 16 rebounds for the Trojans
(5-6, 2-1), who saw a two-game winning streak snapped.

Oregon State trailed 37-28 at the half after a 13-0 USC run in
the final two minutes.

But the Beavers closed the gap in the second half to 46-25 on
Krystal Turner's layup, then took the lead on Mandy Close's fast
break.

Oregon State extended its lead to 70-60, but USC rallied as time
ran down. Eshaya Murphy hit a 3-pointer with four seconds left in
the game as the Trojans fell short.

The Beavers had five players in double figures. Close finished
with 11 points, while Turner and Leilani Estavan both had 10.

The loss left USC coach Chris Gobrecht a win shy of her 50th
victory with the Trojans.
